      Methods in FPP.LinearOptimization.Model.benders with parameters of type Problem 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      private void BendersAlgorithm.addCut​(Problem problem, java.lang.Double[] cut)
      This functions adds the given cut to the given Problem.

      Cut format:
      {1d, 0d, 0d, 7.5d, 50d}
      Last value represents the b column.
      The rest represent coefficient multiplicators.
      The restriction is a <= restriction.

      The given example would look like this:
      1*x1 + 0*x2 + 0*x3 + 7,5*x4 <= 50
      private java.lang.Double[] BendersAlgorithm.calculateAdditionalCut​(Problem problem, java.lang.Double[][] initialTableau)
      This method calculates and returns a cut serving as variable-boundaries for usually not solvable or unbound tableaus.
      private void BendersAlgorithm.stepZeroCut​(MasterProblem masterProblem, SubProblem subProblem, Problem dualProblem, java.lang.Double[] yZeroes)
      This method calculates the first cut in step 0, with all u-values set to 0 and adds the cut to the MasterProblem.

      To set all u-values to 0 all function values are set to 0.
      The SimplexTableau is then solved as usual.
      private void BendersAlgorithm.updateSubproblem​(SubProblem subProblem, Problem dualProblem, java.lang.Double[] y)
      Inserts y-values into function of the DualProblem so that the u-values can be calculated later.
